**Driver Race Pace and Average Position**

```{r}
Abu.Dhabi.Race$Driver <- reorder(Abu.Dhabi.Race$Driver, Abu.Dhabi.Race$Position, FUN = mean)
# Pace Consistency Ridge Plot
ggplot(Abu.Dhabi.Race, aes(x = `LapTime (s)`, y = Driver, fill = Driver)) +
  geom_density_ridges(alpha = 0.7) +
  theme_minimal() + 
  labs(title = "Pace Consistency Ridge Plot") +
  theme(legend.position = "none") 
```
This ridge plot shows the distribution of lap times for each driver. We can compare this plot to the plot below, showing the mean position of each driver. We see a trend between what appears to be the center of these lap times and mean position.

```{r}
# Average Race Position by Driver
avg_pos <- aggregate(Position ~ Driver, data = Abu.Dhabi.Race, mean)
ggplot(avg_pos, aes(x = reorder(Driver, Position), y = Position)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = f1_palette[2]) + coord_flip() +
  theme_minimal() + labs(title = "Mean Position by Driver", x="Driver") 
```

This bar chart shows the mean position of each driver. When comparing it to the plot above, we see a similar shape to the center of the distributions and the way that the bars are aligned to each driver.

**Position Bump Chart and Pit Stops**
```{r}
# Race Position Bump Chart
ggplot(Abu.Dhabi.Race, aes(x = LapNumber, y = Position, color = Driver)) +
  geom_line(size = 1) +
  scale_y_reverse(breaks = 1:20) +
  theme_minimal() + 
  theme(
    legend.position = "bottom", 
    legend.text = element_text(size = 8), 
    legend.title = element_blank()     
  ) +
  guides(color = guide_legend(nrow = 2)) +
  labs(title = "Race Position Bump Chart")
```

This plot shows the position that each driver was in throughout the race, and how it changed. While this plot is very informational, there are some steep decreases that need some context to them. That is why I have included the pit stops below, to help illustrate the reason behind some of the position changes.

```{r}
# Pit Stop Windows
ggplot(subset(Abu.Dhabi.Race, PitStop == TRUE), aes(x = LapNumber, y = Driver)) +
  geom_point(color = f1_palette[2], size = 3) +
  theme_minimal() + labs(title = "Pit Stop Strategy Windows")
```

This is a plot showing what lap the pit stops occurred for each driver. We can see that that sometimes steep drops in the bump chart above coincide with pit stops. We see a large cluster of pit stops between around laps 12-25 and laps 30-45. We see many position drops in these areas of the plot above.




**Permutation Test**

```{r, layout="l-body-outset", echo=FALSE}
knitr::include_graphics("PermutationSlide.png")
```

```{r,eval=FALSE}
Abu.Dhabi.Race$Race_Half <- ifelse(Abu.Dhabi.Race$LapNumber <= 29, "First", "Second")
mean_first <- mean(Abu.Dhabi.Race$`LapTime (s)`[Abu.Dhabi.Race$Race_Half == "First"], na.rm = TRUE)
mean_second <- mean(Abu.Dhabi.Race$`LapTime (s)`[Abu.Dhabi.Race$Race_Half == "Second"], na.rm = TRUE)
difference.in.means.og.sample <- mean_first - mean_second
```

```{r, eval=FALSE}
set.seed(230)
permutation.diff.in.means = NULL

n <- nrow(Abu.Dhabi.Race)
n1 <- sum(Abu.Dhabi.Race$Race_Half == "First")

for(b in 1:10000) {
  shuffled_times <- sample(Abu.Dhabi.Race$`LapTime (s)`, replace = FALSE)
  mean_1 <- mean(shuffled_times[1:n1], na.rm = TRUE)
  mean_2 <- mean(shuffled_times[(n1 + 1):n], na.rm = TRUE)
  permutation.diff.in.means[b] = mean_1 - mean_2
}
```

```{r, eval=FALSE}
((sum(permutation.diff.in.means >= difference.in.means.og.sample) + 1)
/ (length(permutation.diff.in.means) +1))
```

```{r,eval=FALSE}
ggplot() + geom_histogram(aes(x = permutation.diff.in.means, 
                              y= after_stat(density)), bins =  20, 
                          fill = "orange", alpha=0.7) +
  labs(x = "Permutation Values", 
       title = "Permutation Distribution for Difference in Means") +
  geom_density(aes(x=permutation.diff.in.means, color = "blue")) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, col = "blue") + 
geom_vline(xintercept = difference.in.means.og.sample, col = "blue")
```
